ce:section.ce:para:
The synthesis procedure of the probe BPCys was illustrated in Fig. 2
                        . According to the previous work [52], we used 2-hydroxynaphthalene-1,4-dione and benzene-1,2-diamine as the reactants to obtain the intermediate benzo[a]phenazin-5-ol, which was later convinced as the detecting product BPCys-Prod. Subsequently, BPCys-Prod (0.246 g, 1.0 mmol) was dissolved with Et3N (100 μL) in dichloromethane (20 mL). Then the dichloromethane solution (5 mL) of acryloyl chloride (0.225 g, 2.5 mmol) was added dropwise at 0 °C. The reaction was checked by Thin-Layer Chromatography to confirm the completion 2 h later. Finally, the target compound BPCys 0.182 g (yielding 60.6%) was obtained through column chromatography. 1H NMR (600 MHz, DMSO‑d6
                        ) δ 9.41–9.37 (m, 1H), 8.44–8.39 (m, 1H), 8.34–8.29 (m, 1H), 8.10–8.01 (m, 3H), 7.98 (td, J = 7.6, 1.5 Hz, 2H), 7.96 (s, 1H), 6.77 (dd, J = 17.3, 1.0 Hz, 1H), 6.70 (d, J = 10.3 Hz, 1H), 6.36 (dd, J = 10.3, 1.0 Hz, 1H). 13C NMR (151 MHz, DMSO) δ 163.21, 148.84, 142.30, 141.93, 140.43, 139.89, 134.36, 130.42, 130.33, 130.14, 130.07, 128.79, 128.58, 128.23, 127.41, 126.57, 124.58, 121.70, 117.17. HRMS (ESI-TOF m/z): Calculated for [C19H13N2O2]+: 301.0977, Found: 301.0972.
